 "arabic", "text_bw": "HubaAbN", "text_ar": "حُبَابٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HibaAbN", "text_ar": "حِبَابٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maHab~apN", "text_ar": "مَحَبَّةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S) signify the same; (S, K;) i. e., as above. (K.) The degrees of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hub~", "text_ar": "حُبّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are as follow: first,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hawFY", "text_ar": "هَوًى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the “ inclining of the soul, or mind; ” also applied to the “ object of love itself: ” then,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaAqapN", "text_ar": "عَلَاقَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", “ love cleaving to the heart; ” so termed because of the heart's cleaving to the object of love: then,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalafN", "text_ar": "كَلَفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", “ violent, or intense, love; ” from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kulofapN", "text_ar": "كُلْفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifying “ difficulty, or distress, or affliction: ” then,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ei$oqN", "text_ar": "عِشْقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [“ amorous desire; ” or “ passionate love; ”] in the S, “ excess of love; ” and in the language of the physicians, “ a kind of melancholy: ” then,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$agafN", "text_ar": "شَغَفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", “ ardour of love, accompanied by a sensation of pleasure; ” like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lawoEapN", "text_ar": "لَوْعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laAEijN", "text_ar": "لَاعِجٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; the former of which is “ ardour of love; ” and the latter, “ ardent love: ” then,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jawFY", "text_ar": "جَوًى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", “ inward love; ” and “ violence of amorous desire, ” or “ of grief, or sorrow: ” then,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tatay~umN", "text_ar": "تَتَيُّمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", “ a state of enslavement by love: ” then"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tabolN", "text_ar": "تَبْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", “ lovesickness: ” then,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "walahN", "text_ar": "وَلَهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", “ distraction, or loss of reason, in love: ” and then,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huyaAmN", "text_ar": "هُيَامٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "“ a state of wandering about at random in consequence of overpowering love. ” (Kull ubi suprà.) [Accord. to the Msb, it is a simple subst.: but accord. to the K, an inf. n.; and hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hub~FA limaA A^aHobabotumo", "text_ar": "حُبًّا لِمَا اَحْبَبْتُمْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^uHib~u Hub~FA", "text_ar": "اُحِبُّ حُبًّا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I love with loving,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "much, what ye have loved"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Har p. 186.) Hence the phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wakaraAmapF", "text_ar": "وَكَرَامَةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naEamo waHub~apF", "text_ar": "نَعَمْ وَحُبَّةً", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Yea; and with love and honour"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "will I do what thou requirest: or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "for the sake of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "love and honour"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "that I bear thee: or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hb~p", "text_ar": "حبّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may be here used for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hub~FA", "text_ar": "حُبًّا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to assimilate it in termination to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "krAmp", "text_ar": "كرامة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see what follows]. (S, TA.) Hence also the saying of Abu-l-' Atà EsSindee,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "fawaA@ll~`hi maA A^adoriY waA_in~iY laSaAdiqN\n                      \n                     \n                        A^adaA='N EaraAniY mino HubaAbiki A^amo siHoru"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And by God, I know not"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and indeed I am speaking truth"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whether disease have befallen me in consequence of love of thee, or enchantment"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S, TA:) but IB says that the reading best known is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino HibaAbiki", "text_ar": "مِنْ حِبَابِكِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HibAb", "text_ar": "حِباب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", here, may be an inf. n. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAbabotuhu", "text_ar": "حَابَبْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; or it may be pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hub~N", "text_ar": "حُبٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ei$A$N", "text_ar": "عِشاشٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eu$~N", "text_ar": "عُشٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (TA;) or it may be an inf. n. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hababotuhu", "text_ar": "حَبَبْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": some also read ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino HabaAbiki", "text_ar": "مِنْ حَبَابِكِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with fet-h to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "H", "text_ar": "ح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", said to mean"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "on account of the love of thee, and of the main amount thereof:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ham p. 26:) and some read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino janaAbiki", "text_ar": "مِنْ جَنَابِكِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "“ from thy part ” [or “ from thee ”]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HabiybN", "text_ar": "حَبِيبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".       -A2-  Also a Persian word, arabicized, (AHát, S, Msb,) from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xunob", "text_ar": "خُنْب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (AHát, TA,) [or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xubo", "text_ar": "خُبْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xuPo", "text_ar": "خُپْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xaAbiyapN", "text_ar": "خَابِيَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A jar,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, MF,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whether large or small, used for preparing wine:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(MF:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a large jar:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one for water:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IDrd, TA:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "four pieces of wood upon which is placed a two-handled,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "two-eared, jar:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA: [in the CK, by a misplacement of words, this last signification is assigned to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HabaAb", "text_ar": "حَبَاب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":]) pl. [of pauc.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHobaAbN", "text_ar": "اَحْبَابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K) and [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HibaAbN", "text_ar": "حِبَابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HibabapN", "text_ar": "حِبَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, Msb, K.) From this last signification is [said to be] derived the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hub~FA wakaraAmapF", "text_ar": "حُبًّا وَكَرَامَةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[pronounced"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hub~FA wakaraAmaho", "text_ar": "حُبًّا وَكَرَامَهْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A jarstand and a cover"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "will I give thee, or the like],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "krAmp", "text_ar": "كرامة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifying the “ cover ” of a jar, (K, TA,) whether of wood or of baked clay. (TA.) [If this be the true derivation, the phrase may have originated from a person's asking of another the loan or gift of a jar, and the latter's replying “ Yea; and I will give thee a jar-stand and a cover; ” meaning “ I will do what thou requirest, and more: ” but this phrase is now, and perhaps was in early times, generally used, agreeably with the more common significations of the two words, in the sense assigned above to the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hub~apF", "text_ar": "حُبَّةً"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wakaraAmapF", "text_ar": "وَكَرَامَةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]"}], "source_refs": ["A", "Mgh", "TA", "S", "K", "Msb", "MF", "IDrd"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}